==== SOURCE
https://www.the-scientist.com/news-opinion/ai-decodes-speech-and-hearing-based-on-brain-activity-66213
==== AGENT
Shawna Williams
==== GOAL
To develop an AI which Decodes Speech and Hearing Based on Brain Activity
==== DATA
Where did they get their data? What did it look like?
The study was conducted on three people who had arrays of electrodes temporarily implanted in their brains to monitor their brain activity in preparation for surgery for epilepsy
==== METHODS
What did they actually do?
monitored brain activity of what participant heard and said. They hoped to be able to convert a persons imagined speech directly to text, no typing. 
==== RESULTS
How did it go for them?
the project is expected to take upwards of 10 years. 
